HEADWORD: Sennight
<hw>Sen"night</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Contr. fr.
<ets>sevennight</ets>.]</ety> <def>The space of seven nights and days; a
week.</def> <altsp>[Written also <asp>se'nnight</asp>.]</altsp>
<mark>[Archaic.]</mark> <rj><au>Shak.</au> <au>Tennyson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
